allowRecoverability(address).details: By default deriving from AragonApp makes it recoverable

params.token: Token address that would be recovered

allowRecoverability(address).return: bool whether the app allows the recovery

allowance(address,address).details: This value changes when `approve` or `transferFrom` is called.
allowance(address,address).return: the remaining number of tokens that `_spender` is allowed to spend on behalf of `_owner` through `transferFrom`. This is zero by default.

approve(address,uint256).details: The `_amount` argument is the amount of tokens, not shares.
approve(address,uint256).return: a boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded. Emits an `Approval` event.     * Requirements:     * - `_spender` cannot be the zero address. - the contract must not be paused.

balanceOf(address).details: Balances are dynamic and equal the `_account`'s share in the amount of the total Ether controlled by the protocol. See `sharesOf`.
balanceOf(address).return: the amount of tokens owned by the `_account`.

canPerform(address,bytes32,uint256[]).details: Check whether an action can be performed by a sender for a particular role on this app
canPerform(address,bytes32,uint256[]).return: Boolean indicating whether the sender has the permissions to perform the action.        Always returns false if the app hasn't been initialized yet.

decimals().return: the number of decimals for getting user representation of a token amount.

depositBufferedEther().details: This function is separated from submit() to reduce the cost of sending funds.

depositBufferedEther(uint256).details: This function is separated from submit() to reduce the cost of sending funds.

getBeaconStat().return: depositedValidators - number of deposited validatorsbeaconValidators - number of Lido's validators visible in the Beacon state, reported by oraclesbeaconBalance - total amount of Beacon-side Ether (sum of all the balances of Lido validators)

getBufferedEther().details: Buffered balance is kept on the contract from the moment the funds are received from user until the moment they are actually sent to the official Deposit contract.
getBufferedEther().return: amount of buffered funds in wei

getCurrentStakeLimit().details: Special return values: - 2^256 - 1 if staking is unlimited; - 0 if staking is paused or if limit is exhausted.

getELRewardsWithdrawalLimit().return: limit in basis points to amount of ETH to withdraw per LidoOracle report

getInitializationBlock().return: Block number in which the contract was initialized

getPooledEthByShares(uint256).return: the amount of Ether that corresponds to `_sharesAmount` token shares.

getRecoveryVault().details: Get the recovery vault for the app
getRecoveryVault().return: Recovery vault address for the app

getSharesByPooledEth(uint256).return: the amount of shares that corresponds to `_ethAmount` protocol-controlled Ether.

getStakeLimitFullInfo().details: Might be used for the advanced integration requests.
getStakeLimitFullInfo().return: isStakingPaused staking pause state (equivalent to return of isStakingPaused())isStakingLimitSet whether the stake limit is setcurrentStakeLimit current stake limit (equivalent to return of getCurrentStakeLimit())maxStakeLimit max stake limitmaxStakeLimitGrowthBlocks blocks needed to restore max stake limit from the fully exhausted stateprevStakeLimit previously reached stake limitprevStakeBlockNumber previously seen block number

getTotalELRewardsCollected().details: Ether got through LidoExecutionLayerRewardsVault is kept on this contract's balance the same way as other buffered Ether is kept (until it gets deposited)
getTotalELRewardsCollected().return: amount of funds received as execution layer rewards (in wei)

getTotalPooledEther().details: The sum of all ETH balances in the protocol, equals to the total supply of stETH.
getTotalPooledEther().return: the entire amount of Ether controlled by the protocol.

getTotalShares().details: The sum of all accounts' shares can be an arbitrary number, therefore it is necessary to store it in order to calculate each account's relative share.
getTotalShares().return: the total amount of shares in existence.

getUnaccountedEther().details: Gets unaccounted (excess) Ether on this contract balance

handleOracleReport(uint256,uint256).details: periodically called by the Oracle contract

params._beaconBalance: summarized balance of Lido-controlled keys in wei
params._beaconValidators: number of Lido's keys in the beacon state

hasInitialized().return: Whether the contract has been initialized by the time of the current block

initialize(address,address,address,addre.details: As AragonApp, Lido contract must be initialized with following variables:

params._insuranceFund: insurance fund contract NB: by default, staking and the whole Lido pool are in paused state

pad64(bytes).details: Padding memory array with zeroes up to 64 bytes on the right

pauseStaking().details: While accepting new Ether is stopped, calls to the `submit` function, as well as to the default payable function, will revert.    * Emits `StakingPaused` event.

receiveELRewards().details: We need a dedicated function because funds received by the default payable function are treated as a user deposit

resume().details: Staking should be resumed manually after this call using the desired limits

resumeProtocolAndStaking().details: For use in tests to make protocol operational after deployment

resumeStaking().details: Preserves staking limit if it was set previously    * Emits `StakingResumed` event

setELRewardsVault(address).details: Sets the address of LidoExecutionLayerRewardsVault contract

params._executionLayerRewardsVault: Execution layer rewards vault contract address

setELRewardsWithdrawalLimit(uint16).details: Sets limit on amount of ETH to withdraw from execution layer rewards vault per LidoOracle report

params._limitPoints: limit in basis points to amount of ETH to withdraw per LidoOracle report

params._insuranceFeeBasisPoints: basis points go to the insurance fund,
params._operatorsFeeBasisPoints: basis points go to node operators.
params._treasuryFeeBasisPoints: basis points go to the treasury,

setProtocolContracts(address,address,add.details: Oracle contract specified here is allowed to make periodical updates of beacon stats by calling pushBeacon. Treasury contract specified here is used to accumulate the protocol treasury fee. Insurance fund contract specified here is used to accumulate the protocol insurance fee.

params._stakeLimitIncreasePerBlock: stake limit increase per single block

setWithdrawalCredentials(bytes32).details: Note that setWithdrawalCredentials discards all unused signing keys as the signatures are invalidated.

params._withdrawalCredentials: withdrawal credentials field as defined in the Ethereum PoS consensus specs

sharesOf(address).return: the amount of shares owned by `_account`.

submit(address).details: This function is alternative way to submit funds. Supports optional referral address.

symbol().return: the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

toLittleEndian64(uint256).details: Converting value to little endian bytes and padding up to 32 bytes on the right

params._value: Number less than `2**64` for compatibility reasons

totalSupply().details: Always equals to `_getTotalPooledEther()` since token amount is pegged to the total amount of Ether controlled by the protocol.
totalSupply().return: the amount of tokens in existence.

transfer(address,uint256).details: The `_amount` argument is the amount of tokens, not shares.
transfer(address,uint256).return: a boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded. Emits a `Transfer` event. Emits a `TransferShares` event.     * Requirements:     * - `_recipient` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `_amount`. - the contract must not be paused.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: The `_amount` argument is the amount of tokens, not shares.
transferFrom(address,address,uint256).return: a boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded.     * Emits a `Transfer` event. Emits a `TransferShares` event. Emits an `Approval` event indicating the updated allowance.     * Requirements:     * - `_sender` and `_recipient` cannot be the zero addresses. - `_sender` must have a balance of at least `_amount`. - the caller must have allowance for `_sender`'s tokens of at least `_amount`. - the contract must not be paused.

transferShares(address,uint256).details: The `_sharesAmount` argument is the amount of shares, not tokens.
transferShares(address,uint256).return: amount of transferred tokens. Emits a `TransferShares` event. Emits a `Transfer` event.     * Requirements:     * - `_recipient` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have at least `_sharesAmount` shares. - the contract must not be paused.

params._token: Token to be sent to recovery vault

approve(address,uint256).notice: Sets `_amount` as the allowance of `_spender` over the caller's tokens.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).notice: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `_spender` by the caller by `_subtractedValue`.     * This is an alternative to `approve` that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in: https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/token/ERC20/IERC20.sol#L42 Emits an `Approval` event indicating the updated allowance.     * Requirements:     * - `_spender` cannot be the zero address. - `_spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `_subtractedValue`. - the contract must not be paused.

depositBufferedEther().notice: Deposits buffered ethers to the official DepositContract.

depositBufferedEther(uint256).notice: Deposits buffered ethers to the official DepositContract, making no more than `_maxDeposits` deposit calls.

getBeaconStat().notice: Returns the key values related to Beacon-side

getBufferedEther().notice: Get the amount of Ether temporary buffered on this contract balance

getCurrentStakeLimit().notice: Returns how much Ether can be staked in the current block

getELRewardsVault().notice: Returns address of the contract set as LidoExecutionLayerRewardsVault

getELRewardsWithdrawalLimit().notice: Get limit in basis points to amount of ETH to withdraw per LidoOracle report

getOperators().notice: Gets node operators registry interface handle

getStakeLimitFullInfo().notice: Returns full info about current stake limit params and state

getTotalELRewardsCollected().notice: Get total amount of execution layer rewards collected to Lido contract

getWithdrawalCredentials().notice: Returns current credentials to withdraw ETH on ETH 2.0 side after the phase 2 is launched

handleOracleReport(uint256,uint256).notice: Updates beacon stats, collects rewards from LidoExecutionLayerRewardsVault and distributes all rewards if beacon balance increased

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).notice: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `_spender` by the caller by `_addedValue`.     * This is an alternative to `approve` that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in: https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/token/ERC20/IERC20.sol#L42 Emits an `Approval` event indicating the updated allowance.     * Requirements:     * - `_spender` cannot be the the zero address. - the contract must not be paused.

isStakingPaused().notice: Check staking state: whether it's paused or not

pauseStaking().notice: Stops accepting new Ether to the protocol

receiveELRewards().notice: A payable function for execution layer rewards. Can be called only by ExecutionLayerRewardsVault contract

removeStakingLimit().notice: Removes the staking rate limit    * Emits `StakingLimitRemoved` event

resumeStaking().notice: Resumes accepting new Ether to the protocol (if `pauseStaking` was called previously) NB: Staking could be rate-limited by imposing a limit on the stake amount at each moment in time, see `setStakingLimit()` and `removeStakingLimit()`

setFee(uint16).notice: Set fee rate to `_feeBasisPoints` basis points. The fees are accrued when: - oracles report staking results (beacon chain balance increase) - validators gain execution layer rewards (priority fees and MEV)

setProtocolContracts(address,address,add.notice: Set Lido protocol contracts (oracle, treasury, insurance fund).

setWithdrawalCredentials(bytes32).notice: Set credentials to withdraw ETH on ETH 2.0 side after the phase 2 is launched to `_withdrawalCredentials`

submit(address).notice: Send funds to the pool with optional _referral parameter

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Moves `_amount` tokens from the caller's account to the `_recipient` account.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Moves `_amount` tokens from `_sender` to `_recipient` using the allowance mechanism. `_amount` is then deducted from the caller's allowance.
